value.value: Aumento de la concentración de cistationina en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: Concentration of cystathionine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de gamma-glutamilfenilalanina en orina
The amount of gamma-glutamylphenylalanine in the urine, when normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Elevada concentración en sangre de aspartilglucosamina.

definition.value: Concentration of aspartylglucosamine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de sacaropina en orina
The amount of saccharopine in the urine, when normalized to urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Agrandamiento de la placa tectal

definition.value: Abnormal increase in size of the tectal plate (also known as the tectum or the quadrigeminal plate). The tectum is the dorsal portion of the midbrain (brainstem).

value.value: Masa retroperitoneal

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the retroperitoneal region. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Lesión focal hiperintensa del tronco del encéfalo en T1

definition.value: A lighter than expected T1 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brainstem. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the brainstem.

value.value: Fractura subcondral

definition.value: A type of fracture that occurs in the trabecular cancellous bone just beneath the subchondral bone plate without disruption of the articular surface.

value.value: Absceso profundo del cuello

An abscess (i.e., a circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris) localized in the area surrounded by the deep fascia of the neck including the pharynx, larynx, trachea, upper esophagus, thyroid, and parathyroid glands. Infections of pharyngeal, tonsillar, and laryngeal origin affect this space, which includes the parapharyngeal and retropharyngeal spaces.
Agrandamiento epiglótico
Anlarged and edematous epiglottis. This sign can be observed on a lateral radiograph of the neck and it suggests a diagnosis of acute infectious epiglottitis.
Ampliación del espacio prevertebral

Increase in the anterior posterior dimension of the prevertebral space, which is located in the neck region between the anterior part of the cervical spine and the deep layer of the deep cervical fascia running between the transverse processes of the spine.
Engrosamiento del tercer par craneal
Increase in diameter of the third cranial nerve (oculomotor nerve). This feature can be observed by magnetic resonance imaging and may be accompanied by contrast enhancement.
Aumento de la concentración de esfingomielina tisular

definition.value: Concentration of sphoingomyelin in tissues above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Antecedentes de administración reciente de medio de contraste yodado.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: History of recent iodated contrast medium administration

label.value: History of recent iodated contrast medium administration

value.value: Medical history of recent iodinated or radioiodine contrast use.

definition.value: Iodinated contrast media commonly used in various radiologic examinations and interventional procedures results in massive iodide exposure to the thyroid gland. Whereas people with normal thyroids usually experience no ill effects, those with pre-existing thyroid disease may experience thyrotoxicosis (often referred to as thyroid storm in this context), which, if unrecognized, could lead to serious, potentially life-threatening consequences, including atrial arrhythmias, heart failure, pulmonary arterial hypertension, cerebrovascular and pulmonary embolism, and cardiomyopathy.

value.value: Dificultad para pasar la sonda nasogástrica.

Difficulty inserting a nasogastric tube (NGT), a flexible plastic tube that is placed through the nose and esophagus into the stomach and used to administer drugs or for feeding. There are certain circumstances that may make NGT insertion difficult. They are esophageal narrowing, comatose or intubated patients, and patients who have sustained severe facial or skull injuries.
Seno venoso falcino persistente

A falcine sinus that does not involute but persists beyond birth is defined as a persistent falcine sinus. In the 20-mm embryo stage, the primitive falx cerebri contains the sagittal plexus, a meshwork of anastomotic venous channels from which the superior sagittal sinus and straight sinus are thought to develop. A persistent falcine sinus represents a persistent channel of the caudal anastomotic loops of the sagittal plexus.
Pene incircunciso
A medical history in a male of not having been circumcized.

definition.value: Neonatal male circumcision is a common surgical procedure.

value.value: Antecedente de uso de la cosmética facial.
A medical history of use of facial makeup.

definition.value: Facial makeup use may be associated with canaliculitis, which refers to inflammation of the lacrimal canaliculus.

value.value: Sensación de chasquido en la articulación metacarpofalángica

definition.value: A feeling of clicking or snapping at the knuckle (metacarpophalangeal joint) upon extension of flexion of the finger.

value.value: Antebrazo
Avambraccio
Unterarm

definition.value: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the forearm.

value.value: Fractura rotacional

definition.value: A type of displaced fracture in which there has been a rotation of the distal fracture fragment in relation to the proximal portion.

value.value: Localizado sobre prominencias óseas.

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated on the skin in areas where bones are close to the surface (bony prominences).

value.value: Antecedentes de uso de calzado compresivo.
A past medical history of wearing tight shoes, toe-box shoes, or high heel shoes.

definition.value: This may be a risk factor for Morton neuroma.

value.value: Disminución de la turgencia de la piel.
Reduced skin turgor means reduced elastic recoil of the skin to its normal contour after being pinched in a fold.
Consumo reciente de hongos forrajeros
Medical history of recently eating wild mushrooms.
Progresión de proximal a distal

definition.value: Refers to symptomatology that begins in the proximal limbs and subsequently affects the distal limbs.

value.value: Disociación autonómica-voluntaria de los movimientos faciales.

The selective paralysis of voluntary fascio-pharyngo-glosso-masticatory movements with preservation of reflexive and automatic functions is referred to as autonomic-voluntary dissociation, which is a distinctive feature of Anterior opercular syndrome (also known as Foix-Chavany-Marie syndrome).

definition.value: The patient cannot open or close the mouth, protrude the tongue or close the eyes to orders, but can smile, cry, yell or yawn automatically. Ischemia is the most frequent cause and it is generally due to bilateral opercular lesions, but bilateral subcortical lesions have also been reported. In the anterior opercular syndrome the connections be-tween the motor cortex and the V, VII, IX, XII cranial nuclei and brainstem are interrupted bilaterally. Emotional and spontaneous movements, dependent on extrapyramidal connections, thalamus and hypothalamus, are preserved (automatic-voluntary dissociation).

value.value: Masa en la mandíbula

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the jaw. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Exposición nocturna excesiva a la luz
Exposure to continuous light at night, including night-shift work or a nocturnal lifestyle.
Menstruaciones entre la menarquia y la menopausia

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Menstruating female between menarche and menopause

label.value: Menstruating female between menarche and menopause

definition.value: Past medical history of a woman who is menstruating, i.e., not premenstrual or post-menopause.

value.value: Rotura prematura de membranas en el prematuro
PPROM (preterm premature rupture of membranes) occurs at less than 37 weeks of gestation. PPROM can happen spontaneously, during preterm labor, or following a procedure such as amniocentesis.
Antecedentes de cirugía abdominal.

definition.value: A past medical history that indicates that the patient had a surgical procedure involving the abdomen.

value.value: Engrosamiento de la membrana de Descemet

definition.value: The thickness of the Descement membrane is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Blocco di branca destra incompleto
Bloqueo incompleto de rama derecha
Unvollständiger Rechtsschenkelblock

Right bundle branch block (RBBB) represents an abnormality in the intraventricular electrical conduction system of the human heart, generating enlarged QRS and modified vectors on the electrocardiogram (ECG). Incomplete RBBB (IRBBB) is defined by (i) QRS duration between 110 and 120 ms in adults; (ii) rsr, rsR, or rSR in leads V1 or V2. The R or r deflection is usually wider than the initial R wave. In a minority of patients, a wide and often notched R wave pattern may be seen in leads V1 and/or V2; (iii) S wave of greater duration than R wave or greater than 40 ms in leads I and V6 in adults; and (iv) Normal R peak time in leads V5 and V6 but greater than 50 ms in lead V1. The first 3 criteria should be present to make the diagnosis. When a pure dominant R wave with or without a notch is present in V1, criterion 4 should be satisfied.

definition.value: Right bundle branch block appears with a prevalence of 3% to 7% in the general population, more frequently in men than in women.

value.value: Inicio perimenopáusico

definition.value: Onset of signs or symptoms of disease during the period of a woman's life shortly before the occurrence of the menopause.

value.value: Inicio posmenopáusico

definition.value: Onset of signs or symptoms of disease during the period of a woman's life after the occurrence of the menopause.

value.value: Monoplejía espástica
Spastic weakness found in only one upper or lower extremity.
Patrón de atenuación en mosaico en el pulmón

definition.value: Mosaic attenuation pattern in the lung is a term used to describe regions of differing pulmonary attenuation on CT imaging. It is a non-specific finding, although is associated with several conditions such as obstructive small airway disease, occlusive vascular disease (in which case is called mosaic perfusion pattern), pulmonary edema, and parenchymal diseases.

value.value: Relación aldosterona:renina elevada

The ratio of aldosterone concentration to renin concentration is above the upper limit of normal. If aldosterone is expressed in ng/dl and plasma renin activity is expressed as ng/ml/hr, then values above 20 with aldosterone level above 15 are considered indicative of primary aldosteronism.
Meteorismo

An increase in the gas content inside the bowel associated with distension of the abdomen and hydroaeric noises. The most common symptom of meteorism is a bloated sensation. It may be associated with abdominal discomfort. Some individuals may also complain of a distended stomach and excessive belching and/or passage of flatus.
Ausencia de la elevación del amoníaco durante el ejercicio isquémico

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Failure to elevate ammonia on ischemic exercise

label.value: Failure to elevate ammonia on ischemic exercise

value.value: Normal subjects display an increase in the concentration of ammonia in the blood following an ischemic exercise test. This term refers to an increase in ammonia that is below the lower limit of normal.
Hipertensión lábil

definition.value: Frequent fluctuations of blood pressure between normal and high levels, changing more dramatically than normal.

It is normal for BP to fluctuate from moment to moment and from day to day. BP fluctuation is related to many factors such as physical activity, emotion, position, respiratory cycle, diet, salt intake, alcohol ingestion, sleep deprivation, and others. Even in otherwise normotensive individuals, BP fluctuation can be substantial during moments of physical or emotional stress or even without overt provocation.

label.value: Absent axon flare response after intradermal histamine injection

value.value: Ausencia de respuesta de flare axonal tras la inyección intradérmica de histamina

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Absent axon flare response after intradermal histamine injection

value.value: The axon reflex (also known as the flare response) is a response that is stimulated by peripheral nerves of the body that travels away from the nerve cell body and branches to stimulate target organs. In the human skin, there are three different phenomena mediated by axon reflex mechanism; flare, sweating and pilomotion. Stroking or intradermal injection of histamine or substance P into the human skin pro- duces widespread vasodilatation (flare) and plasma extravasation (wheal). This term refers to the failure of intradermal hista injection to elicit flare.
Disminución de las respuestas simpatoneurales a la prueba de presión en frío

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Reduced sympathoneural responses to the cold pressor test

label.value: Reduced sympathoneural responses to the cold pressor test

value.value: Response to the cold pressor test below the lower limit of normal. The cold pressor test is a simple and validated test in which the subject immerses one hand or foot into ice water for 1 to 3 minutes while blood pressure (BP) and heart rate are monitored. The cold stimulus activates afferent sensory pathways that, in turn, trigger a sympathetic response resulting in an increase in BP.
Prueba positiva de antígeno de Giardia en materia fecal
Fecal analysis for Giardia antigen is abnormal. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.
Pérdida excesiva de sangre durante el parto.

Loss of a substantial amount of blood during delivery (some definitions stipulate 1000 ml or more), typically associated with manifestations such as low blood pressure, a rapid heart rate, dizziness, light-headedness, fatigue, and weakness.
Vegetaciones de válvulas cardíacas.

Endocarditis infection occurs along the edges of the heart valves. Damage to the cardiac endothelium followed by platelet and fibrin deposition results in a sterile lesion known as nonbacterial thrombotic endocarditis (NBTE) or vegetation. Microbes entering the bloodstream via routine or invasive procedures adhere to the vegetation and are engulfed in an outer meshwork of fibrin and platelets. Subsequent rapid microbial multiplication in a protected area of impaired host defense leads to vegetation growth and continuous bacteremia.
Caja torácica plana
The anteroposterior dimension of the chest on the lateral radiograph is often relatively narrow compared with the chest width on the frontal radiograph.
Ausencia de zona pelúcida.
Lack of the oocyte extracellular matrix region (zona pellucida). This feature can be observed following follicular aspiration (retrieval of eggs for fertility treatments).

definition.value: During in vitro fertilization treatment, oocyte retrieval is performed after ovarian stimulation via vaginal puncture. Cumulus-oocyte complexes, which consist of cumulus cells surrounding the centrally located oocyte, are isolated from the individual's follicular fluid. This term refers to the finding of oocytes lacking zonae pellucidae.

value.value: Prolapso del cordón umbilical

The presence of the umbilical cord (UC) between the fetal presenting part and the cervix, regardless of the membrane status (intact or ruptured). Descent of the UC through the cervix is essential for diagnosing cord prolapse. It can be either overt (past the presenting part) or occult (alongside the presenting part).
